 Harold O. Zimman, philanthropist, member of the U.S. Olympic Committee and 
publisher of sports magazines, died at 78 of heart failure in Boston. . . . 
U.S. World Cup goalkeeper Tony Meola has signed with the Buffalo Blizzard of 
the indoor National Professional Soccer League. 
