</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of compact discs and audio cassettes for the week 
ended Dec. 14, compared to sales of the previous week and the same week of 
1993, in millions of units sold: 
</P>
<P>
 Latest week Albums: 21.2 Singles: 1.9 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago Albums: 15.9 Singles: 1.8 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago Albums: 19.6 Singles: 2.5 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Guerinot, former A&M Records marketing executive and current manager of 
multimillion-albumselling band Offspring, has signed a five-year deal with BMG 
for a new "custom" label. The imprint will be financed and distributed by BMG's 
successful Arista label.The deal was personally handled by newly appointed BMG 
Entertainment North America President and CEO Strauss Zelnick, reversing a long 
trend of unconcluded negotiations undertaken by the German-based media 
conglomerate. 
</P>
