ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: AST RESEARCH APPOINTS VP TO HEAD TEXAS MANUFACTURING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gary D. Weaver has been appointed vice president of Texas manufacturing for 
Irvine-based AST Research Inc. Weaver will oversee all manufacturing operations 
in AST's Fort Worth, Texas, facility, which produces desktop and server 
computers. Before joining the company, he was vice president of operations for 
Ioptex Research Inc. in Irwindale.He has also been senior vice president of 
operations for Irwin Magnetics Systems Inc., vice president of operations for 
Cipher Data Products, which acquired Irwin in 1989, and managing director for 
Atari Far East. 
</P>
<P>
 * Robert J. Bard has been appointed vice president for regulatory and legal 
affairs at I-Flow Corp., an Irvine manufacturer of medical devices. Bard joined 
the company in 1988 as manager of regulatory affairs, quality assurance and 
quality control and was promoted to director in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jim Janusz has been appointed worldwide director of customer support for 
Platinum Software Corp., an Irvine financial software company. Before joining 
Platinum, Janusz was director of technical systems support at Symbol 
Technologies Inc. 
