EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; L.A. MAN ARRESTED ON 2 COUNTS OF 
BURGLARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A commuter burglar who broke into two Simi Valley businesses before dawn 
Thursday was arrested as he headed home to Los Angeles, Simi Valley Police Sgt. 
Gordon Weeks said. 
</P>
<P>
 The crime matches a pattern Simi Valley detectives say is becoming familiar -- 
Los Angeles County thieves come to Simi Valley, rip off property or cars, and 
zip home along the Simi Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Villanueva, 24, was booked at the Ventura County Jail in lieu of 
$20,000 bond on two counts of burglary, jail officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Weeks said a shop owner at an industrial complex in the 200 block of Easy 
Street called police just after 4 a.m. to say he saw someone smash a window at 
a neighboring business and steal property from inside. 
</P>
<P>
 Dispatchers broadcast a description of the suspect and his car, and Officer 
Don Douglass arrested Villanueva several minutes later as he drove east on the 
freeway, Weeks said. 
</P>
<P>
 A clock and a watch reported stolen from Richard Evans Construction were found 
in Villanueva's car, but there was no sign of sewing machines that were 
reported stolen from a neighboring business, Weeks said. MACK REED 
</P>
