<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNFIRE WOUNDS 2 BOYS IN SANTA ANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gunfire from someone on a bicycle wounded two boys Thursday night, a police 
sergeant said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified boys were standing in front of a house in the 1400 block of 
South Maple Street when a gunman opened fire, striking one of the boys in the 
thigh and the other in the foot, said Sgt. Dick Faust. The boys did not see the 
assailant, whose gunfire also hit a house two doors down, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both boys were listed in good condition Thursday night at Coastal Communities 
Hospital.  
</P>
<P>
 "They were lucky, real lucky," Faust said. "It could have been much worse." 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators say the shooting may be gang-related. Police have no suspects 
and are continuing the investigation. 
</P>
