</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAGUNA SEEKS TO FILL VACANCIES ON PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE EARNEST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking applicants for the Planning Commission and Design Review 
Board. 
</P>
<P>
 One Planning Commission seat was vacated when voters elected then-Commissioner 
Paul Freeman to the City Council.Also, terms expire Feb. 1 for one alternate 
and three regular Design Review Board members.  
</P>
<P>
 The Planning Commission reviews and makes recommendations to the City Council 
regarding land use within Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners spend at least four to six hours each week on city business, 
including attending meetings on the second and fourth Wednesdays of each month 
at 7 p.m. They are paid $60 monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 The Design Review Board also serves as the Board of Adjustment, considering 
requests for zoning code variances and coastal development permits. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members spend about 10 hours a week fulfilling their duties, including 
attending meetings most Thursdays at 6:30 p.m. They are paid $120 per month. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the city clerk's office. They must be returned 
to the city by Jan. 3. The City Council will interview applicants and make 
their appointments Jan. 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 497-0302. LESLIE EARNEST 
