ANGELS' SNOW UNDERGOES SHOULDER SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angel first baseman J.T. Snow underwent arthroscopic surgery on his left 
shoulder Thursday at Anaheim Memorial Hospital.The surgery was to repair a 
partial tear of cartilage in the shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
 Snow was injured while diving for a fly ball when playing left field in the 
Venezuelan Winter League. He is expected back for the start of spring training. 
</P>
<P>
 Also Thursday, former Angel reliever Joe Grahe signed a triple-A contract with 
the Colorado Rockies with an option for the 1996 season. Grahe became a free 
agent in November when the Angels attempted to outright him to their triple-A 
Vancouver roster. 
