<TEXT>
<P>
 Steve Tampus made a three-point shot at the buzzer to give College of the 
Canyons a 70-69 victory over El Camino in the first round of the Cypress 
tournament on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons (4-6) trailed by 11 at halftime but Mars Crain scored 16 of his 19 
points during the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 77, Fullerton 76 -- Valley held off a late Fullerton surge to win the 
first-round Crown City tournament game. 
</P>
<P>
 Vernon Simmons had 16 points and 10 rebounds, Ricky Steele had 15 points and 
10 rebounds, and Lamarr Thompson added 15 points for Valley (10-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 95, Contra Costa 88 -- Orville Turner had 28 points and 12 
rebounds to lead Antelope Valley to a first-round victory in the Sequoias 
tournament. Brandon McIntire added 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
 BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 102, Blair 46 -- The Falcons, ranked No. 1 in the Times' 
regional poll, improved to 8-0 in the final round of pool play of the Crescenta 
Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Brock Jacobsen led the way with 33 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists, and 
Nate Sinning added 30 points. Blake Jacobson had 10 points, and Jake Willis had 
17 assists to go with five points. 
</P>
<P>
 Poly 65, San Gabriel 55 -- Polo Gonzalez scored 20 points and Jaime Cerna 
added 17 for the Parrots in Crescenta Valley tournament pool play. 
