<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR BEATS LAKEWOOD TO ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mandy Clayton, Andree Verhulst and Melissa Schutz each scored 10 points as 
Newport Harbor defeated Lakewood, 56-33, Thursday in the semifinals of the 
Cypress tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, sixth-ranked in The Times Orange County preseason poll, plays 
Costa Mesa in tonight's final. Schutz also had nine rebounds for the Sailors 
(6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the other semifinal: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 61, Harbor City Narbonne 46 -- Koo Kim scored 21 points and Corri 
Lurmann added 15 for Costa Mesa (6-2), which 34-18 at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 In consolation games of the Bolsa Grande Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 44, South Torrance 29 -- Tamara Inoue had 20 points, five assists 
and eight steals and Tayyiba Haneef added eight points to lead Laguna Hills 
(5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 64, Bolsa Grande 22 -- Michelle Tuazon had 13 points, including three 
three-point baskets, and Andrea Picchi had 13 points and nine rebounds to lead 
Magnolia (6-1). Lien Mai scored 10 points for Bolsa Grande (2-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In pool play of the El Dorado Co-ed Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 Downey 67, Sunny Hills 16 -- Angela Gonzalez scored 10 points for Sunny Hills 
(0-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Corona 50, Valencia 28 -- Jamie Snavely scored nine points for Valencia (2-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In the first round of the Orange Lutheran tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Century 55, Connelly 31 -- Addy Alexander scored 12 points and Nina Alexander 
added eight points, 10 rebounds and six assists to lead Century (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 53, Liberty Christian 22 -- Alana Kempton had 14 points to 
lead Whittier Christian (5-2), which led 18-2 after the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 In first round of the Valley Christian tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 49, Bellflower 44 -- Brooke Donberg had 13 points and Allison 
Fulp added 12 points and 13 rebounds for Los Alamitos (3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 73, El Toro 33 -- Marie Philman scored 27 points, grabbed 12 rebounds 
and had eight steals for Edison (4-2), which led, 29-19, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 47, Cerritos 40 -- Jennifer Ludwicki scored 12 points to lead 
Fountain Valley (5-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 42, El Modena 35 -- Nadia Hoerner had 18 points and 11 rebounds to 
lead Fullerton (4-4).  
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 47, Los Altos 38 -- Brooke Koehler scored 14 points and Jo Berchtold 
added 11 points for host La Habra (3-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Loara 48, Anaheim 23 -- Paola Flores had 18 points and six assist to lead 
Loara (3-3). 
</P>
</TEXT>
