<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL LA QUINTA CLASSIC; OCEAN VIEW TAKES EARLY LEAD, CRUISES PAST 
LA QUINTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ocean View jumped to a 23-6 lead after the first quarter and cruised the rest 
of the way, beating host La Quinta, 62-42, Thursday in pool play of the Lady 
Aztec Classic girls' basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Jennifer Tuiolosega scored a game-high 22 points and junior Becky 
Fraser added 21 points, hitting seven of seven from the free-throw line for the 
Seahawks (5-4).Junior Andrea Tuiolosega had 10 points for Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Shum had 17 points, including four three-pointers, and Jaclyn Fredrickson 
added 11 for La Quinta (0-6). 
</P>
<P>
 The Seahawks will face Esperanza in the championship, at 7:30 tonight. The 
Aztecs beat Ocean View last week by four points. 
</P>
<P>
 In other pool play games: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 83, Norwalk John Glenn 29 -- By the end of the half, Esperanza led 
by 31 points. Esperanza's Leah Combs had a game-high 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Theresa Gethins added 14 and forward Lindsay Brown had 12 points for 
the Aztecs, who improve to 8-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 40, Santiago 31 -- Janea Butler had 13 points and five rebounds and Dinah 
Shah had five points, four assists and three steals for Troy (6-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Alejandra Torres scored 13 points and Angie Chin-Sam added eight points and 13 
rebounds for Santiago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
