<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES 1994 FALL ALL-COUNTY TEAMS; ALL-COUNTY GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 JILL BUTTS 
</P>
<P>
 Setter 
</P>
<P>
 Edison, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Butts was named Sunset League Most Valuable Player after leading the Chargers 
to a banner season. At 5-10, Butts is an aggressive setter with deft defensive 
skills. She has orally committed to Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 JENNY KESSY 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Kessy, the South Coast League Most Valuable Player, helped the Dolphins win 
their second consecutive league title. Kessy is a dangerous attacker from 
anywhere on the court. She has orally committed to USC. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 MISTY MAY 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 May is one of the county's most coveted players ever. She played outside 
hitter for the Sailors, who won the school's first Division I State title, but 
will probably set in college. She has orally committed to Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 COURTNEY OWENS 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Although playing at a small school, Owens received major attention from 
recruiters. A dynamic hitter who led the Eagles to their first State girls' 
volleyball championship, she has orally committed to Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 MELISSA SCHUTZ 
</P>
<P>
 Middle blocker 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Sailor Coach Dan Glenn called Schutz the best middle attacker he has coached. 
Schutz was named co-MVP of the Sea View League with May. Both were four-year 
starters. Schutz has orally committed to Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 MELISSA WENDT 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6-2, Wendt was one of Orange County's best offensive players, and one of 
the few who could carry a team through portions of a match. She helped 
Huntington Beach finish the best season in school history. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 DAVE MOHS 
</P>
<P>
 Coach of the year 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 
</P>
<P>
 In his 12th and final year, Mohs led Edison to the most successful season in 
school history. Edison won the Sunset League -- one of the county's toughest -- 
and advanced to the section semifinals and State quarters. 
</P>
