<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vons Names New Advertising Agency: The Arcadia-based grocery chain, as part of 
an effort to change its image to attract price-conscious consumers, named 
Dailey & Associates of Los Angeles, a unit of Interpublic Group, to handle 
advertising for its Vons, Pavilions and Expo units. The account was formerly 
handled by DDB Needham of Los Angeles. Billings for it are estimated to be 
between $15 million and $20 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121694-0218 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 108727 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 16, 1994, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
68 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John B. DeNault was named to succeed founder Louis W. Foster as chairman of 
20th Century Industries Inc. . . . Canada's Parliament passed a law approving 
the Uruguay Round of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. . . . Santa 
Monica Hospital Medical Center confirmed that it is considering merging with or 
selling the facility to either St. John's Hospital & Health Center or UCLA 
Medical Center. 
</P>
