<TEXT>
<P>
 Mortgage Rates Hit 3-Year High: Thirty-year, fixed-rate mortgages averaged 
9.25% this week, up from 9.15% last week, according to a national survey 
released by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. It was the highest since Aug. 
9, 1991, when the average was 9.27%.The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in 
October, 1993. On one-year, adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders were asking an 
average initial rate of 6.75%, up from 6.56% last week. Fifteen-year mortgages, 
a popular option for those refinancing mortgages, averaged 8.89% this week, up 
from 8.77% a week earlier. The rates do not include add-on fees known as 
points. 
