<TEXT>
<P>
 Judge Approves Manville Asbestos Plan: U.S. District Judge Jack Weinstein of 
Brooklyn OKd a second attempt to save the cash-strapped Manville trust, 
approving a plan under which more than 100,000 claimants will initially get 10 
cents on the dollar for asbestos-related injuries. Weinstein said in a 222-page 
decision that the plan will ensure that all claimants are compensated to some 
degree. The restructuring also increases the trust's assets by at least $1 
billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
