<HEADLINE>
<P>
KCAL, KTTV, KFWB TOP THE FIELD AT GOLDEN MIKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KCAL-TV Channel 9, KTTV-TV Channel 11 and KFWB-AM(980) were the big winners 
Thursday in the 45th annual Golden Mike Awards for outstanding broadcast news 
in Southern California. Each captured eight honors for work done during the 
past year. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners will be honored at a dinner at the Universal Hilton on Jan. 21. 
While most of them were announced in advance by the Radio & TV News Assn. of 
Southern California, winners in several categories remain to be unveiled that 
night, including best radio and TV newscasts among large stations. 
</P>
<P>
 KCAL won Golden Mikes for weather, sports news reporting, serious feature 
reporting, light feature reporting, entertainment reporting, videotape editing 
of a single feature story, writing and news special ("Earthquake! What We Know 
Now"). 
</P>
<P>
 KTTV's awards were in the categories for best documentary ("California AIDS 
Ride," a tie with KNSD-TV in San Diego), news reporting, investigative 
reporting, economic reporting, videography of a single news feature, 
videography of a feature series or special, videotape editing of a hard news 
series or special and original news commentary, news analysis, station 
editorial or series of editorials. 
</P>
<P>
 KEYT-TV Channel 3 in Santa Barbara and KNSD-TV Channel 39 in San Diego each 
won four Golden Mikes, while KMEX-TV Channel 34 in Los Angeles earned three. 
KSBY-TV in San Luis Obispo won the award for best daytime newscast among small 
stations. 
</P>
<P>
 In the radio competition, all-news KFWB captured awards for writing, sports 
news reporting, sports feature reporting, spot news, live coverage of a news 
story, investigative reporting, light feature reporting and best continuing 
coverage of the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 KNX-AM (1070) was the runner up with six awards. KFI-AM (640) was honored for 
best news broadcast under 15 minutes among large stations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
