<P>
BANDS TO GO 'BEHIND CURTAIN' TO HELP HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A dozen local bands will play from noon to midnight on Sunday to raise money 
for Children's Hospital of Orange County in a "Christmas Behind the Curtain" 
concert. 
</P>
<P>
 The benefit, which includes performances by former Dramarama singer John 
Easdale and the Cadillac Tramps offshoot band, Rule 62, will take place at the 
Tunnel dance club, 612 N. Eckhoff St., Orange.The benefit is part of the club's 
live alternative rock concert series dubbed The Kurtain. Admission: $7. 
Information: (714) 630-6128. 
</P>
