<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121694-0306 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 108815 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 16, 1994, Friday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Valley Life; Page 29; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
321 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLUB SCENE: CLOSE-KNIT AND CASUAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHERIE SAUNDERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To say this is a family bar would be an understatement. This is a place where 
the regulars welcome you as if you're a long-lost relative. By the end of the 
night, not only will you know their names, you'll know where they live, their 
Social Security numbers, mothers' maiden names. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 THE SCENE: The place is small, with booths on the left, tables in the middle 
and the bar to the right. A game area is in the front, with one pool table, two 
dartboards, a pinball machine and several video games. Two TV sets hang on 
either end of the bar area and a small stage sits at the far end of the room. 
</P>
<P>
 THE CROWD: Strictly an after-work, blue-collar crowd, meaning lots of jeans, 
flannel, sweat shirts and T-shirts. Although you'd only need two hands to count 
the number of people this particular Wednesday, the group was lively in its 
conversations at the bar, as well as enthusiastic about the live entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 MUSIC: A jukebox is available to fill in the lulls between the live 
entertainment ranging from blues to rock. Karaoke is featured Tuesdays and 
Sundays, live bands Thursdays to Saturdays. Wednesday nights belong to 
bluesy-folk singer/musician Mary White. She is a favorite among the regulars, 
who often request her original tunes. 
</P>
<P>
 THE GOOD: Tom Baetz, 43, has been a regular for eight years. "This is an oasis 
for me after a long day of working for the state," said the Van Nuys resident. 
"I can come here and feel like it's home. It's my 'Cheers,' but don't you dare 
say I'm Norman." 
</P>
<P>
 THE BAD: The dance floor, if that's what it is, has room for maybe five 
couples if they're willing to keep their movements to a minimum. Also, there's 
only one pool table. 
</P>
<P>
 THE WORD: "I used to like that song until I heard someone do it on karaoke 
night," said a patron at the bar.  
</P>
<P>
 McRed's Cocktail Lounge, 13235 Victory Blvd., Van Nuys. Open 8 a.m. to 2 a.m. 
daily. No cover. (818) 980-2845. CHERIE SAUNDERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
